com.intland.codebeamer.remoting

Interface RemoteApi

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.rmi.Remote

    public interface RemoteApi
extends java.rmi.Remote
    Defines the CodeBeamer RemoteService API.

    Please note: all methods throw IllegalStateException if there is no RemoteSession is active or that has expired.

      • findTrackerItemsByFilter

        TrackerItemDto[] findTrackerItemsByFilter(java.lang.String token,
                                        java.lang.Integer[] trackerIds,
                                        java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.Collection<java.lang.String>> orFilters,
                                        java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.Collection<java.lang.String>> andFilters,
                                        java.util.Date changedSince,
                                        int page,
                                        int pageSize)
        Find the specified page of issues in the specified trackers matching the (choice field) filters and/or modified in the last X days.

        Each filter entry reads as: field IN (value, ... , value), an empty value ("") means unset/empty/null.

        Example: 

        
        Map<String,Collection<String>> filters = ...;
        filters.put(Integer.valueOf(TrackerLayoutLabelDto.STATUS_LABEL_ID), Arrays.asList("New", "Resolved"));
        filters.put(Integer.valueOf(TrackerLayoutLabelDto.PRIORITY_LABEL_ID), Arrays.asList("High", "Low"));
        filters.put(Integer.valueOf(TrackerLayoutLabelDto.RESOLUTION_LABEL_ID), Arrays.asList("Resolved", "Fixed"));
        filters.put(Integer.valueOf(TrackerLayoutLabelDto.SUBMITTED_BY_LABEL_ID), Arrays.asList("bond", RoleDto.PROJECT_ADMIN));
        filters.put(Integer.valueOf(TrackerLayoutLabelDto.ASSIGNED_TO_LABEL_ID), Arrays.asList("", RoleDto.DEVELOPER, "zsolt"));

        For reference fields, e.g. "Versions", the field values must be entity references (ReferenceDto.toString() or interwiki link ids (ReferableDto.getInterwikiLink(): 

        
        filters.put(Integer.valueOf(TrackerLayoutLabelDto.VERSION_LABEL_ID), Arrays.asList("[ITEM:4711]", "9-4712"));

        Since CB-6.0 you can also specify filters for non-choice fields. In this case the first parameter can optionally be the comparison operator. If no comparison operator is specified "IN" is implied. For all comparison operators except "IN" and "NOT IN" only the first parameter will be used. 

        
        filters.put(Integer.valueOf(TrackerLayoutLabelDto.NAME_LABEL_ID), Arrays.asList("like", "%Introduction%"));
        filters.put(Integer.valueOf(TrackerLayoutLabelDto.getCustomFieldId(1)), Arrays.asList("IN", "de", "en", "it));
        Parameters:
        token - is the remote session identifier
        trackerIds - is an array of tracker ids where to search for issues
        orFilters - is a Map of (choice field) filters, where key = choice field ID and value is a Collection of choice value names or ids, where at least one filter (if any) must match.
        andFilters - is a Map of (choice field) filters, where key = choice field ID and value is a Collection of choice value names or ids, where all filters (if any) must match.
        changedSince - date is optional, filters for issues which are changed since the given date
        page - is the number of the result page to return, first page is 0.
        pageSize - is the number of items per page (Maximum 1000 items per page will be returned)
        Returns:
        the specified page of issues in the specified trackers matching the (choice field) filters and/or modified in the last X days
        Since:
        5.4.3

      • batch

        RemoteApi.BatchMethodResult[] batch(RemoteApi.BatchMethodCall[] calls)
        Call several methods of the remote-api in a batch on the server, and return a result of each in an array. This is better in performance if you need to download several pieces of information from the server, because the HTTP connection overhead and communication overhead can be significantly reduced. All methods in the BatchMethodCall is called in the order of the "calls" array. If exeption is thrown that is caught, and will be returned in the RemoteApi.BatchMethodResult object, and then still the rest of the methods are called.
        Parameters:
        calls - The method calls to be executed on the server
        Returns:
        The result of each call in the same order as they are in the "calls" argument
